{"parse":{"title":"master","pageid":58145,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Master|máster|màster|Mäster|mäster}}\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈmɑːs.tə/|a=RP}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈmas.tə/|q2=influenced by RP|/ˈmɑːs.tə/|a=Northern England}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈmas.təɹ/|a=Scotland,Ireland}}\n* {{enPR|măsʹtər|a=GA}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈmæs.tɚ/}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈmɑs.tə/|a=Southern US,AAVE,obsolete}} {{q|see {{m|en|marster}}}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈmaːs.tə/|a=AU,NZ}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-master.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-master.wav|a=Southern England}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɑːstə(ɹ)|æstə(ɹ)|s=2}}\n* {{hyphenation|en|mas|ter}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{etymon|en|id=maister|:inh|enm:maister|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|maister}}, {{m|enm|mayster}}, {{m|enm|meister|pos=noun}} and {{m|enm|maistren|pos=verb}}, from {{inh|en|ang|mǣster}}, {{m|ang|mæġster}}, {{m|ang|mæġester}}, {{m|ang|mæġister}}, {{m|ang|magister|t=master}}, from {{der|en|la|magister|t=chief, teacher, leader}}, from {{der|en|itc-ola|magester}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*méǵh₂s}} (as in {{m|la|magnus|t=great}}, also cognate of {{cog|en|much}} and {{m|en|mickle}}) + {{m|la|-ester}}/{{m|la|-ister}} (compare {{m|la|minister|t=servant}}). Reinforced by {{der|en|fro|maistre}}, {{m|fro|mestre|pos=noun}} and {{m|fro|maistriier}}, {{m|fro|maister|pos=verb}} from the same Latin source. Compare also {{cog|stq|Mäster|t=master}}, {{cog|fy|master|t=master}}, {{cog|nl|meester|t=master}}, {{cog|de|Meister|t=master}}. {{doublet|en|maestro|magister|meister}}.\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alt|en|maistre||archaic}}\n* {{alt|en|Marse|marse||obsolete|dialectal|US|Caribbean}}\n* {{alt|en|mas'r||dated|pronunciation spelling|representing southern US black English}}\n* {{alt|en|Master}}\n* {{alt|en|mastre|maister|mayster||obsolete}}\n* {{alt|en|Massa|massa|massah|massy|masta|Mastah|mastah|mastuh||pronunciation spellings}}\n* {{alt|en|measter||obsolete|UK|pronunciation spelling}}\n* {{alt|en|mester|mister||dialectal}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# Someone who has [[control]] over something or someone.\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1881|author=w:Benjamin Jowett|title=w:Thucydides\n|passage=We are '''masters''' of the sea.}}\n#* {{RQ:Milton Paradise Regained|book=Samson Agonistes|page=83|lines=415–420|passage='''Maſter'''s commands come with a power reſiſtleſs / To ſuch as owe them abſolute ſubjection; / And for a life who will not change his purpoſe? / (So mutable are all the ways of men) / Yet this be ſure, in nothing to comply / Scandalous or forbidden in our Law.}}\n#* {{RQ:Spectator|VI|535|13 November 1712|97|When I have thus made myself '''master''' of a hundred thousand drachmas {{...}}.}}\n#* {{RQ:Churchill Celebrity|chapter=IV|pages=58–59|pageref=58|passage=The Celebrity, by arts unknown, induced Mrs. Judge Short and two other ladies to call at Mohair on a certain afternoon when Mr. Cooke was trying a trotter on the track.{{...}}Their example was followed by others at a time when the '''master''' of Mohair was superintending in person the docking of some two-year-olds, and equally invisible.}}\n# The owner of an [[animal]] or [[slave]].\n# {{lb|en|nautical}} The [[captain]] of a [[merchant ship]]; a [[master mariner]].\n#: {{syn|en|skipper|captain}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1896|author=Rudyard Kipling|title=[[s:The Seven Seas/The Mary Gloster|The Mary Gloster]]\n|passage='''Master''' at two-and-twenty, and married at twenty-three—}}\n# {{lb|en|dated}} A [[male]] [[head of household]].\n# Someone who [[employ]]s others.\n#* {{RQ:Churchill Celebrity|chapter=IV|page=46|passage=No matter how early I came down, I would find him on the veranda, smoking cigarettes, or otherwise his man would be there with a message to say that his '''master''' would shortly join me if I would kindly wait.}}\n# {{senseid|en|expert}}An [[expert]] at something.\n#: {{syn|en|Thesaurus:skilled person}}\n#: {{ux|en|Mark Twain was a '''master''' of fiction.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en |author=<nowiki>[</nowiki>{{w|Thomas Babington Macaulay}}<nowiki>]</nowiki>|journal=w:The Edinburgh Review |year=1843 |month=July |number=CLVII |title=Art. VII—''The Life of Joseph Addison''. By Lucy Aikin. |page=231 |pageurl=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.228407/page/n245/mode/1up |text=But that which chiefly distinguishes Addison from Swift, from Voltaire, from almost all the other great '''masters''' of ridicule, is the grace, the nobleness, the moral purity, which we find even in his merriment.}}\n#* {{RQ:Locke Education|189\n|passage=No care is taken to improve young men in their own language, that they may thoroughly understand and be '''masters''' of it.}}\n#* {{quote-av|en|writer=w:George Lucas|title=[[w:Star Wars (film)|Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope]]|year=1977|passage={{w|Darth Vader}}: I've been waiting for you, Obi-Wan. We meet again, at last. The circle is now complete. When I left you I was but the learner; now I am the '''master'''.<br>{{w|Obi-Wan Kenobi}}: Only a '''master''' of evil, Darth.}}\n#* {{quote-book\n|en\n|year=2001\n|chapter=People with Cancer\n|title=Falun Gong Stories: A Journey to Ultimate Health\n|url=https://archive.org/details/isbn_9781931035057/\n|location=\n|publisher=Golden Lotus Press\n|ISBN=1-931035-05-9\n|OCLC=155384434\n|page=62\n|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/isbn_9781931035057/page/62/\n|text=A turning point came earlier this year. In January 2000, the local Qigong '''master''' who treated me asked me to find Falun Gong material on the Internet for him.}}\n#* {{see more citations|en}}\n# A [[tradesman]] who is qualified to [[teach]] [[apprentice]]s.\n# {{lb|en|dated}} A [[male]] [[schoolteacher]].\n# {{senseid|en|skilled artist}}A skilled [[artist]].\n# {{lb|en|dated}} A man or a boy; [[mister]]. See [[Master]].\n#* {{RQ:Swift Directions to Servants|passage=Where there are little '''Maſters''' and Miſſes in a Houſe, they are uſually great Impediments to the Diverſions of the Servants;}}\n# A [[master's degree]]; a type of [[postgraduate]] [[degree]], usually undertaken after a [[bachelor]] degree.\n#: {{syn|en|masters|master's|magistrate|q3=Quebec}}\n#: {{ux|en|She has a '''master''' in psychology.}}\n# A person holding such a [[degree]].\n#: {{ux|en|He is a '''master''' of marine biology.}}\n# The [[original]] of a [[document]] or of a [[recording]].\n#: {{ux|en|The band couldn't find the '''master''', so they re-recorded their tracks.}}\n# {{lb|en|by extension|music}} The [[copyright]] in a [[sound recording]].\n#: {{ux|en|Many modern recording artists value owning their '''masters'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|film}} The [[primary]] [[wide shot]] of a [[scene]], into which the [[closeup]]s will be edited later.\n#: {{syn|en|establishing shot|long shot}}\n# {{lb|en|legal}} A parajudicial officer (such as a referee, an auditor, an examiner, or an assessor) specially appointed to help a court with its proceedings.\n#: {{ux|en|The case was tried by a '''master''', who concluded that the plaintiffs were the equitable owners of the property.{{...}}}}\n# {{lb|en|engineering|computing}} A [[device]] that is [[control]]ling other devices or is an authoritative source.\n#: {{syn|en|coordinator|primary}}\n#: {{ant|en|secondary|slave|worker}}\n#: {{ux|en|a '''master''' wheel}}\n#: {{ux|en|a '''master''' database}}\n# {{lb|en|freemasonry}} A person holding an office of authority, especially the presiding officer.\n# {{lb|en|by extension}} A person holding a similar office in other civic societies.\n# {{ellipsis of|en|master key}}.\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2020|author=Jane M. Wiggins|title=Facilities Manager's Desk Reference|page=517\n|passage=The use of '''masters''' and submasters will enable suites of rooms to be controlled by one key.}}\n# {{lb|en|BDSM}} A [[male]] [[dominant]].\n#: {{cot|en|mistress}}\n\n=====Hyponyms=====\n* {{l|en|mistress}} {{qualifier|feminine-specific form}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{lookfrom|en|master}}\n{{col4|en|dancing master's kit||archmaster|baggagemaster|balletmaster|bandmaster|bargemaster|battlemaster|beachmaster|beastmaster|Beefmaster|blogmaster|boatmaster|bodymaster|botmaster|bowmaster|bridgemaster|burghermaster|caddiemaster|caddymaster|campmaster|cellarmaster|chapelmaster|chargemaster|chartermaster|cheermaster|chimesmaster|choirmaster|chorusmaster|clubmaster|coachmaster|coalmaster|craftmaster|Cubmaster|divemaster|drawmaster|fagmaster|firemaster|flockmaster|foragemaster|forgemaster|fuckmaster|funkmaster|gangmaster|grillmaster|guildmaster|herbmaster|horsemaster|hostmaster|huntmaster|hutmaster|keymaster|loremaster|masterate|masterbatch|masterbit|masterbrand|Mastercard|mastercraftsman|masterer|mastergroup|masterji|masterlike|masterling|masterman|masterpoint|masterpost|mastersmith|mastertone|masterweaver|masterwort|mintmaster|mixmaster|multimaster|nonmaster|outmaster|partymaster|pathmaster|piermaster|pitmaster|Playmaster|pledgemaster|portmaster|poundmaster|premaster|pressmaster|propmaster|quarrymaster|quaymaster|quotemaster|rackmaster|rangemaster|ravenmaster|reckonmaster|roadmaster|roastmaster|runemaster|salesmaster|Scoutmaster|signalmaster|slammaster|slavemaster|sockmaster|spellmaster|spinmaster|spookmaster|stablemaster|strokemaster|studmaster|submaster|swordmaster|swordsmaster|towmaster|troncmaster|truckmaster|wagonmaster|wardmaster|warmaster|waymaster|weaponmaster|wharfmaster|whipmaster|winemaster|woodmaster|wordmaster\n|master's thesis|honorary master\n|serve two masters\n|ballet master\n|barmaster\n|beemaster|master of game|master of the woods\n|bergmaster\n|boroughmaster\n|brewmaster||want must be one's master\n|burghomaster,burgomaster\n|master butter knife\n|one's own master|Master of the Mint\n|bushmaster|charter master|ditto master\n|cashmaster|cube master\n|chess master,chessmaster\n|cockmaster\n|concertmaster\n|craftsmaster\n|dockmaster|master out\n|dogs have masters, cats have staff\n|dragonmaster| master of ceremony\n|drill master,drillmaster\n|dungeon master\n|games master,games-master\n|Grand Master\n|harbor master,harbour master,harbor-master,harbormaster\n|headmaster\n|house master,housemaster\n|ironmaster\n|jack of all trades, master of none\n|jumpmaster\n|Comacine master\n|master craftsman,master-craftsman\n|master-slave manipulator\n|use the master's tools to dismantle the master's house\n|loadmaster\n|lockmaster\n|master-at-arms\n|master baiter\n|master bedroom|master bathroom\n|master bricklayer\n|master builder\n|master card\n|master cast\n|master caution\n|master class\n|master clock\n|master copy\n|master cylinder\n|masterdom\n|masterfast\n|master file\n|masterful\n|master gland\n|masterhood\n|master key\n|masterless\n|masterly\n|master mariner\n|master mason\n|mastermind\n|Master of Arts\n|master of ceremonies\n|Master of Science\n|masterous\n|masterpiece\n|master plan,master-plan,masterplan\n|master race|master boot record\n|Masters\n|master sergeant\n|mastership\n|master signifier,master-signifier\n|mastersinger\n|master status\n|masterstroke\n|master tradesman\n|master trust\n|master warning\n|masterwork\n|mastery\n|metal master\n|mint-master\n|old master\n|past master,passed master\n|paymaster\n|postmaster\n|property master,prop master,props master\n|puppet master,puppet-master,puppetmaster\n|quartermaster\n|question-master\n|quizmaster\n|rattlesnake master\n|ringmaster\n|roaming master\n|saymaster\n|schoolmaster\n|scoutmaster\n|shedmaster\n|sheepmaster\n|shipmaster\n|spymaster\n|stationmaster\n|taskmaster\n|toastmaster\n|trackmaster\n|trailmaster\n|trainmaster\n|undermaster\n|watermaster\n|webmaster\n|weighmaster\n|whoremaster\n|workmaster\n|wreck master,wreck-master,wreckmaster\n|yardmaster\n|barge master\n|boarding-master\n|charge description master\n|chargemaster,charge-master,charge master\n|game master\n|garret-master\n|gold master,golden master\n|grandmaster,grand master\n|job master\n|lord and master\n|master of all one surveys\n|master of one's time\n|master of the horse\n|master of the mint\n|master of the obvious\n|master of the schools\n|no one is born a master\n|posture-master\n|sailing-master\n|shipping master\n|special master\n|spirit master\n|taxing master\n|thigh master\n|vendue master\n|writing master\n|zombie master}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n* {{l|en|mistress}} {{qualifier|feminine form of \"master\"}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n{{top2}}\n* {{desc|srn|masra}}\n* {{desc|as|মাষ্টৰ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|bn|মাষ্টার|মাস্টার|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ca|màster|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fi|master|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fr|master|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|de|Master|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|gu|માસ્તર|bor=1}}\n** {{desc|sd|ماستَرُ//मास्तरु|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|inc-hnd|bor=1}}\n** {{desc|hi|मास्टर}}\n** {{desc|ur|ماسْٹَر}}\n* {{desc|ks|ماسٹَر|ماشٹَر|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|mr|मास्तर|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ne|मास्टर|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|pl|master|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|pt|máster|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|pa|bor=1}}\n*: {{desc|pa|ਮਾਸਟਰ|sclang=1}}\n*: {{desc|pa|ماسْٹَر|sclang=1}}\n* {{desc|es|máster|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|tr|master|bor=1}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|someone who has control over something or someone}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|pronar|m}}, {{t|sq|zotni}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|سَيِّد|m}}\n* Aromanian: {{t|rup|domnu}}, {{t|rup|afendu}}\n* Basque: {{t|eu|jabe}}\n* Belarusian: {{t+|be|гаспада́р|m}}, {{t|be|валада́р|m}}, {{t|be|хазя́ін|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|господа́р|m}}\n* Buryat: {{t|bua|эзэн}}, {{t|bua|эжэн}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|mestre|m}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|主人|tr=zhǔrén}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|pán|m}}\n* Daur: {{t|dta|ejin}}\n* Esperanto: {{t+|eo|mastro}}, {{t|eo|reganto}}\n* Estonian: {{t+|et|isand}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|herra}}, {{t+|fi|isäntä}}\n* Franco-Provençal: {{t|frp|maîtro|m}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|maître|m}}\n* Friulian: {{t|fur|paron|m}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|amo|m}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|ბატონი}}, {{t+|ka|მბრძანებელი}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Meister}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|κύριος|m}}, {{t+|el|αφέντης|m}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|ἄναξ}}, {{t|grc|δεσπότης}}, {{t|grc|κοίρανος}}, {{t|grc|μεδέων}}, {{t|grc|πρύτανις}}, {{t|grc|κύριος}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|स्व